Comment: This queen move could have been premature - but I liked it because it seemed aggressive.
I capture his pawn with check. I can force him to move his king now, preventing castling.
I exchange, forcing the King to move.
White prepares to "castle manually", with the threat of a discovered check.
I castle out of the way.
Opening a line for his bishop.
Prevents a check on his king. Not sure if this is the best square for the bishop though - ...Re8 pins it.
I connect my rooks by moving my bishop out of the way.
White develops his knight, protecting against ...Bxf2 followed by the loss of the h2 pawn. Looks quite cramped around his king now.
White moves his king out of the way.
I push my knight forward to avoid it being pinned against my rook by Bg5.
Threatening to take one of my pawns (h7 or f7).
